    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - SINGLE REDUCTION, SINGLE SPEED AXLES: SPICER D135-S,
        F155-S, F170-S SERIES - ASSEMBLE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>ASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="8">
            <title>DIFFERENTIAL</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s14014_14.xml" xrefid="f1401411">Figure 11</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If ring gear was removed from differential case, re-install at this time. Use hydraulic
                    or mechanical press and suitable riveting fixture (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401431">Figure 31</hotlnk>). Pressure requirement per rivet is 20 to 25 U.S. tons
                    (18.1 to 22.7 metric tons) for the D135-S, and 45 to 50 U.S. tons (41 to 45 metric tons) for the
                    F155-S and F170-S.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401431" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401431" filename="../figg14/G1401431.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 31. Riveting Ring Gear</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install bearing cones to differential case halves (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401432">Figure 32</hotlnk>). Place bearing cups on cones during remainder of
                    assembly to prevent damage to bearings.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401432" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401432" filename="../figg14/G1401432.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 32. Bearing Cone Installation</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply a small amount of axle lubricant to all mating surfaces (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401433">Figure 33</hotlnk>). This will keep thrust washers in place during
                    assembly and provide initial lubrication.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401433" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401433" filename="../figg14/G1401433.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 33. Lubricate Mating Surfaces</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place thrust washer and side gear in left hand differential case (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401434">Figure 34</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401434" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401434" filename="../figg14/G1401434.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 34. Thrust Washer &#38; Side Gear Reassembly</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Assemble differential pinions and thrust washers on cross shaft (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401435">Figure 35</hotlnk>). Place assembly in left hand differential case.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401435" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401435" filename="../figg14/G1401435.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 35. Pinions and Thrust Washer on Cross Shaft</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place remaining side gear and thrust washers in position on differential pinions (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401436">Figure 36</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401436" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401436" filename="../figg14/G1401436.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 36. Side Gear and Thrust Washer Placement</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Assemble case halves,
                    <emph type="bold">making sure match marks are lined up</emph>(
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401437">Figure 37</hotlnk>)
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401437" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401437" filename="../figg14/G1401437.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 37. Assemble Case Halves</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>If case halves were not match marked, align the quadrants that have the three machined
                            holes.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install case bolts and nuts. Tighten alternately and evenly to 75 to 90 ft-lbs. (101 to
                    122 N&#8226;m) (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401438">Figure 38</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401438" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401438" filename="../figg14/G1401438.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 38. Case Bolts &#38; Nuts Assembly</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install side bearing cones to differential case hubs.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Use of a press and proper adapter is preferred to eliminate possible damage to the
                            bearings.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
